    <ownedClass>
        <class isAbstract="false" name="Specimen">
            <derivationSupplier className="Role" staticModelDerivationId="1"/>
            <graphicRepresentation presentation="HL7">
                <graphElement containerDiagramName="Main"
                    isHeightAutoSize="false" isWidthAutoSize="false"
                    shapeId="Sheet.1" shapeTemplate="Role">
                    <position x="4.91" y="1.6775"/>
                    <size height="3.44612" width="2.50184"/>
                </graphElement>
            </graphicRepresentation>
            <annotations>
                <constraint name="Specimen">
                    <text>
                        <p>classCode is SPEC or ISLT</p>
                    </text>
                    <graphicRepresentation>
                        <graphElement containerDiagramName="Main"
                            isHeightAutoSize="true"
                            isWidthAutoSize="true" shapeId="Sheet.134">
                            <position x="3.74294" y="0.93456"/>
                            <size height="0.32778" width="1.51413"/>
                            <anchorage connectToShapeId="Sheet.1">
                                <position x="4.5" y="1.09845"/>
                                <graphEdge>
                                    <anchor>
                                    <position x="5.16018" y="1.6775"/>
                                    </anchor>
                                </graphEdge>
                            </anchorage>
                        </graphElement>
                    </graphicRepresentation>
                </constraint>
                <otherAnnotation type="html">
                    <text>
                        <P>
                            <B>This Specimen CMET is derived from the R_Specimen [Universal] in the HL7 v3 ballot. It is designed to be used for general Laboratory requests and reports without the overhead of the requirements of Automation or Specimen Tracking. It is constrained for use with Human subjects and excludes environmental, non-human and manufactured specimens. The 'Specimen' may play the role of a Specimen or an Isolate.</B>
                        </P>
                    </text>
                </otherAnnotation>
            </annotations>
            <attribute conformance="R" isMandatory="true"
                isStructural="true" maximumMultiplicity="1"
                minimumMultiplicity="1" name="classCode" sortKey="1">
                <annotations>
                    <otherAnnotation type="html">
                        <text>
                            <p>Indicates the role being played by the entity.</p>
                            <p>Entities in the Specimen CMET may play the role of either a 'Specimen' or an 'Isolate'. The Role Class identifies the type of role being played by the entity in a particular message. </p>
                            <p>Valid role types are 'SPEC' or 'ISLT' according to the entity playing the role.</p>
                            <p>Where 'SPEC' is used, the code shall be taken from the Snomed National Specimen Type subset.</p>
                            <p>Where 'ISLT' is used, the code shall be taken from the Snomed National_Lab Isolate subset_UK20060401.</p>
                        </text>
                    </otherAnnotation>
                </annotations>
                <derivationSupplier attributeName="classCode"
                    className="Role" staticModelDerivationId="1"/>
                <type name="CS"/>
                <supplierDomainSpecification codingStrength="CNE" domainName="SPEC"/>
            </attribute>
            <attribute conformance="R" isMandatory="true"
                maximumMultiplicity="1" minimumMultiplicity="1"
                name="id" sortKey="2">
                <annotations>
                    <otherAnnotation type="html">
                        <text>The ID is the unique identifier for the <i>Specimen/Isolate</i>.<br/>
                            <br/>According to the use of the CMET, the ID may be a Placer or a Fulfiller identifier for the Specimen/Isolate. In Request interactions, it shall be the Placer identifier, in Event interactions, it shall be the Fulfiller identifier. In Event interactions, provision is made to carry the Placer Identifier in an associated role (SpecimenAlternateIdentifier) in addition to the Fulfiller identifier where one is available. The ID is made up of two parts, a root and extension. The Root will be an OID allocated to the system that generates the extension and will be at such a level that the combination of the Root and Extension is universally unique. The extension will be a human readable string generated by the system and may not be unique across the whole system.<br/>
                            <br/>E.g. There are many systems that are configured on a departmental basis and the same range of human readable strings are used in multiple departments. In such cases, the Root OID shall be allocated at such a level that the human readable portion is unique within that Root OID.<br/>
                            <br/>&lt; id root =" 9.99.999.99.10.2 " extension ="B05.00504885C "/&gt;<br/>
                            <br/>Where 9.99.999.99. identifies the Hospital organization and 9.99.999.99.10.2 identifies the ID scheme within the Laboratory system that generated the extension B05.00504885C <br/>
                            <br type="_moz"/>
                        </text>
                    </otherAnnotation>
                </annotations>
                <derivationSupplier attributeName="id" className="Role" staticModelDerivationId="1"/>
                <type name="II" typeSpecialisation=""/>
            </attribute>
            <attribute conformance="R" fixedValue="P" isMandatory="true"
                maximumMultiplicity="1" minimumMultiplicity="1"
                name="code" sortKey="3">
                <annotations>
                    <otherAnnotation type="html">
                        <text>
                            <p>Fixed value of 'P' Indicates that the role is a Patient related or derived specimen rather than a Q.A. or Pooled specimen</p>
                        </text>
                    </otherAnnotation>
                </annotations>
                <derivationSupplier attributeName="code"
                    className="Role" staticModelDerivationId="1"/>
                <type name="CE"/>
                <supplierDomainSpecification codingStrength="CNE" domainName="SpecimenRoleType"/>
            </attribute>
        </class>
    </ownedClass>
    <ownedClass>
        <class isAbstract="false" name="Process">
            <derivationSupplier className="Procedure" staticModelDerivationId="1"/>
            <graphicRepresentation presentation="HL7">
                <graphElement containerDiagramName="Main"
                    isHeightAutoSize="true" isWidthAutoSize="true"
                    shapeId="Sheet.11" shapeTemplate="Act">
                    <position x="9.65735" y="4.61672"/>
                    <size height="1.18112" width="3.36768"/>
                </graphElement>
            </graphicRepresentation>
            <annotations>
                <designComments>
                    <text>
                        <p>Principally for the Collection Process.</p>
                        <p>Could also be used to identify source</p>
                        <p>of an isolate such as Anaerobic culture.</p>
                        <p>May be an Act Ref within message.</p>
                    </text>
                    <graphicRepresentation>
                        <graphElement containerDiagramName="Main"
                            isHeightAutoSize="true"
                            isWidthAutoSize="true" shapeId="Sheet.104">
                            <position x="13.7" y="2.47623"/>
                            <size height="0.72222" width="1.99495"/>
                            <anchorage connectToShapeId="Sheet.11">
                                <position x="14.69748" y="2.83734"/>
                                <graphEdge>
                                    <anchor>
                                    <position x="12.68826" y="4.61672"/>
                                    </anchor>
                                </graphEdge>
                            </anchorage>
                        </graphElement>
                    </graphicRepresentation>
                </designComments>
                <otherAnnotation type="html">
                    <text>
                        <P>
                            <B>This is the process by which the 'specimen' was obtained</B>
                        </P>
                    </text>
                </otherAnnotation>
            </annotations>
            <attribute conformance="R" fixedValue="PROC"
                isMandatory="true" isStructural="true"
                maximumMultiplicity="1" minimumMultiplicity="1"
                name="classCode" sortKey="5">
                <annotations>
                    <otherAnnotation type="html">
                        <text>
                            <p>Indicates that this is a procedure.</p>
                        </text>
                    </otherAnnotation>
                </annotations>
                <derivationSupplier attributeName="classCode"
                    className="Procedure" staticModelDerivationId="1"/>
                <type name="CS"/>
                <supplierDomainSpecification codingStrength="CNE" domainName="PROC"/>
            </attribute>
            <attribute conformance="R" isMandatory="true"
                isStructural="true" maximumMultiplicity="1"
                minimumMultiplicity="1" name="moodCode" sortKey="6">
                <annotations>
                    <otherAnnotation type="html">
                        <text>
                            <P>May be Intent or Event. It is not used in Request mood in order to request that the Lab collect. Here it would be in Event mood as the decision that the lab shall collect has been made.</P>
                            <P>It may be in Intent mood where it has yet to be collected by the sender and they wish to indicate the time at which they intend to collect the specimen.</P>
                            <P>It is not intended that this is ever used to place an 'Order' for collection, merely to identify the collection process.</P>
                        </text>
                    </otherAnnotation>
                </annotations>
                <derivationSupplier attributeName="moodCode"
                    className="Procedure" staticModelDerivationId="1"/>
                <type name="CS"/>
                <supplierDomainSpecification codingStrength="CNE" domainName="x_ActMoodIntentEvent"/>
            </attribute>
            <attribute conformance="R" isMandatory="true"
                maximumMultiplicity="1" minimumMultiplicity="1"
                name="id" sortKey="7">
                <annotations>
                    <otherAnnotation type="html">
                        <text>
                            <p>A globally unique UUID by which this act could be referenced in future.</p>
                        </text>
                    </otherAnnotation>
                </annotations>
                <derivationSupplier attributeName="id"
                    className="Procedure" staticModelDerivationId="1"/>
                <type name="II" typeSpecialisation="II.NPfIT.uuid.mandatory"/>
            </attribute>
            <attribute conformance="R" isMandatory="true"
                maximumMultiplicity="1" minimumMultiplicity="1"
                name="code" sortKey="8">
                <annotations>
                    <designComments>
                        <text>&lt;p&gt;Subset: "SNOMED lab collection method subset_UK_20060401"&lt;/p&gt;</text>
                    </designComments>
                    <otherAnnotation type="html">
                        <text>
                            <p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0cm 0cm 0pt">
                                <span lang="EN-US">A value taken from SNOMED lab collection method subset_UK_20060401</span>
                            </p>
                            <p>For most specimens, this will be a generic concept of "17636008 specimen collection (procedure)". Where the collection method is specialised such as a 'Timed collection' or a method such as 'Clean Catch', 'Bag', 'Mid-stream' (applied to Urine collection), Biopsy etc, appropriate SnCT codes from the SNOMED lab collection method subset_UK_20060401 shall be used.</p>
                        </text>
                    </otherAnnotation>
                </annotations>
                <derivationSupplier attributeName="code"
                    className="Procedure" staticModelDerivationId="1"/>
                <type name="CE"/>
                <supplierDomainSpecification codingStrength="CNE" domainName="SnomedCT"/>
            </attribute>
            <attribute conformance="R" defaultValue="completed"
                isMandatory="true" maximumMultiplicity="1"
                minimumMultiplicity="1" name="statusCode" sortKey="13">
                <annotations>
                    <otherAnnotation type="html">
                        <text>
                            <P>Set to 'completed' as the process has been defined.</P>
                        </text>
                    </otherAnnotation>
                </annotations>
                <derivationSupplier attributeName="statusCode"
                    className="Procedure" staticModelDerivationId="1"/>
                <type name="CS"/>
                <supplierDomainSpecification codingStrength="CNE" domainName="ActStatus"/>
            </attribute>
            <attribute conformance="R" isMandatory="false"
                maximumMultiplicity="1" minimumMultiplicity="1"
                name="effectiveTime" sortKey="14">
                <annotations>
                    <designComments>
                        <text>&lt;p&gt;DT of collection&lt;/p&gt;</text>
                    </designComments>
                    <otherAnnotation type="html">
                        <text>
                            <p>The actual or intended time of collection of the specimen. This may be an interval in the case of timed collections such as 24 hour collection (Start time - End time). In some circumstances, the Snomed concept for the collection process and the actual interval in the effective time may differ. The effective time or time interval shall be the time used for any calculation.</p>
                        </text>
                    </otherAnnotation>
                </annotations>
                <derivationSupplier attributeName="effectiveTime"
                    className="Procedure" staticModelDerivationId="1"/>
                <type name="IVL">
                    <supplierBindingArgumentDatatype name="TS"/>
                </type>
            </attribute>
        </class>
    </ownedClass>
    <ownedClass>
